fields.title: Home page
fields.content:
Niwi.Be - Andrei Antoukh

Niwi.Be is a kind of web / blog that I use as a platform to publish documentation and other items of personal interest, such as links, snippets, news, etc ...

The source for this page is available under BSD LICENSE. (To access a repository see footnote).

You can get more information about me in the About section.

fields.title: About
fields.content:
Name: Andrei Antoukh
Location: Madrid (Spain)
Twitter: @niwibe
GitHub: github.com/niwibe
### Small description: ### I specialize in web development, real time applications and infrastructure design for high scalability. In my job, I usually working with python and django, but I like to experiment with other technologies that I look "interesting". ### My interests are: ### * **Operating System**: FreeBSD and Linux
* **Programming language**: Python2/3 and JavaScript
* **Databases**: PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis and CouchDB
* **Version control**: git and mercurial
#### Other technology stack: #### And a long list of other tools with which to work or play every day often: * celery * gevent * nodejs * zeromq * nginx * lighttpd * jQuery * tornado * flask * apache * C++/Qt4 * MySQL My contributions to the opensource world: ### My photo: ###
